review: I went into the consultation thinking that my tooth has to be removed, that there is no saving it since I had ignored it for so long, it was badly damaged. But I was pleasantly surprised as the Doctor explained to me that the tooth can be saved quite easily. I got the Root Canal Treatment started in next appointment, I was expecting to be in pain after the procedure, but it went quiet smooth, tooth was a bit sore but there was no hindress with eating, sleeping or work. Gave about 3 days for the tooth to heal and then got the filling done. RCT was complete. Going back to get the cap/crown placed, it will strengthen the tooth further. I feel relieved and now have a positive attitude towards oral care. I am very thankful to Dr. Farooq for giving me the confidence to get my tooth healed and for working on it with so much care.

tags: Treatment satisfaction,
